entry.title: Unidentified
entry.content: We do not know what this plant is. Tightly clumped circle 40cm in diameter, 10cm high, of shiny green elongated leaves 4-7cm long. Mass of leaves with lots of flowers hidden under the leaves. Flowers are hooded, cup-like 3-4cm long with a thick white column inside. White base with purple hood. Plant appears to be connected with roots, not bulbs.

entry.title: Comesperma ericinum
entry.content: Really unusual form in this swamp. Only two records locally, 20km either side of this one, and both from about 1890. ID by NW.

entry.title: Leptospermum continentale
entry.content: Verging on L. scoparium on some plants (eg. pic1) but leaves broadest at base and tapering to tip as per L. continentale (see especially pic2). Unusual forms of many species in this swamp.
